text: Barela is a town and nagar panchayat in Jabalpur district in the state of Madhya Pradesh, India. Barela has an average literacy rate of 70%, higher than the national average of 59.5%; with 59% of the males and 41% of females literate. 14% of the population is under 6 years of age. ==References== Category:Cities and towns in Jabalpur district
